ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it with Prof. Guinnane your first semester! Otherwise, you might have to take it third year, with quals, presentations, and TAing duties. Then it can get difficult.

very good course even for people not interested in economic history because the teacher makes the subject interesting by class discussions and applying basic economic principles to various historical contexts.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Got me more interested in international trade and made me appreciate econ more since I did not do that much applied work. I was also an undergrad math major, so this backgroundmaterial really helped.Another plus of this course is that though I don't intend to study history, the topics were cool and, in some sense, provided inspiration for the study of economics. It made me appreciate the growth, demand, and repeated games models when I saw them applied.
I am now more aware of economic history as a field of study and the course gave me a broad idea about important facts and debates inEuropean economic history.
